10920 
10921 
10922 
10923 WCHAR ff_convert (  /* Converted code, 0 means conversion error */
10924     WCHAR   src,    /* Character code to be converted */
10925     UINT    dir     /* 0: Unicode to OEMCP, 1: OEMCP to Unicode */
10926 )
10927 {
10928     const WCHAR *p;
10929     WCHAR c;
10930     int i, n, li, hi;
10931 
10932 
10933     if (src < 0x80) {   /* ASCII */
10934         c = src;
10935     } else {
10936         if (dir) {      /* OEMCP to unicode */
10937             p = oem2uni;
10938             hi = sizeof(oem2uni) / 4 - 1;
10939         } else {        /* Unicode to OEMCP */
10940             p = uni2oem;
10941             hi = sizeof(uni2oem) / 4 - 1;
10942         }
10943         li = 0;
10944         for (n = 16; n; n--) {
10945             i = li + (hi - li) / 2;
10946             if (src == p[i * 2]) break;
10947             if (src > p[i * 2])
10948                 li = i;
10949             else
10950                 hi = i;
10951         }
10952         c = n ? p[i * 2 + 1] : 0;
10953     }
10954 
10955     return c;
10956 }

10958 #error This file is not needed in current configuration.

10960 #endif
